What does IAM give you?
-   Centralized control over your AWS account
-   Shared Access to your AWS account
-   Granular permissions
-   Identity Federation (including Active Directory, Facebook, LindenIN, etc)
-   Multifactor Authentication
-   Provides  temporary access for users/devices and services,as necessary
-   Allows you to setup up your own password rotation policy
-   Supports PCI DSS compliance (Payment Gateway)

Critical Terms:
Users - end users
Groups - A collection of users under one set of permissions
Roles - You can create roles and can then assign them to AWS resources
Policies - A document that defines one (or more) permissions

